25. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 2017445025
T1  - A Study of the Effect of Metformin Versus Myo-Inositol in the Management of PCOS - A Randomised Controlled Trial
A1  - Roy S.B. 
Y1  - 2020//
N2  - Of the common hormonal disorders in females of childbearing age-group, polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is the most important. It is associated with various morbidities like type-II diabetes mellitus, obesity, insulin-resistance, cardiovascular dysfunctions and is characterised by reproductive and psychological manifestations, resulting in an enormous impact on health. The objective of our study was to compare the efficacy of metformin and myo-inositol on certain parameters such as BMI reduction, LH/FSH ratio (suggesting insulin resistance) and HOMA-IR Index in PCOS patients. In our study, both metformin and myo-inositol significantly reduced the BMI. Metformin also significantly reduced the insulin resistance and improved insulin-sensitivity. It also significantly improved menstrual pattern in the women with PCOS. These changes were not observed when treated with myo-inositol. The sample size calculation was done with n Master 2.0 Christian Medical College, Vellore.Copyright © 2020 Indian Medical Association. All rights reserved.
