AN  - 637099252
ID  - 35057707 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=35057707]
T1  - D-Chiro-inositol and PCOS: between myth and reality. The never-ending story
A1  - Cianci A.
A1  - Vitale S.G. 
AO  - Vitale, Salvatore Giovanni; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6871-6097
Y1  - 2022//
N2  - Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is one of the most common disorders among women of reproductive age and can be diagnosed when at least two of the following criteria are present: chronic ovulatory disorder, clinical and/or biochemical hyperandrogenism, and polycystic ovaries. Diet and lifestyle modifications are the main therapeutic intervention and they can fully restore ovary function and avoid PCOS consequences in a certain number of patients. However, prescription of medications or dietary supplements is often needed. The literature has confirmed the significant role of inositol therapy in PCOS, with particular reference to Myo-inositol and D-chiro-Inositol. The aim of this review is to clarify the use of inositols for the treatment of PCOS and the recent scientific theories about D-Chiro-Inositol properties as an ovarian aromatase inhibitor.
