90. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 638513198
T1  - Comparative study of myoinositol plus D-chiro inositol versus metformin in PCOS patients
T3  - Royal College of Obstretriscians and Gynaecologists World Congress, RCOG 2022. London United Kingdom.
A1  - Pakhale S.
A1  - Batham A.
A1  - Sehra A.
A1  - Bharadwaj S. 
Y1  - 2022//
N2  - Background: Insulin resistance with dysfunction of hypothalamic-pituitary- ovarian- axis is key etiological factor for manifestations of PCOS. Myo-inositol and D-chiro- inositol, both stereoisomers of inositol are useful as insulin sensitizer drugs. However, evidence on its efficacy over metformin, an older drug used for PCOS, is insufficient in Indians. Objective(s): comparing effectiveness of myo-inositol plus d-chiro inositol versus metformin based on biochemical and hormonal parameters, ovarian morphology (ovarian volume and follicular count) on ultrasonography. Design(s): Prospective randomized controlled study. Method(s): 50 PCOS patients received Tab MYCHIRO (myo-inositol 550mg plus d-chiro 150mg) twice daily for 3 months; 50 patients received 500mg metformin twice daily for 3 months. Outcome measured as LH/FSH ratio, fasting and postprandial blood sugar, fasting and postprandial insulin, serum testosterone, HOMA-IR and ultrasonography done initially and post-treatment. Statistical analysis was done using SPSS 13 software. p-value less than 0.05 was considered significant. Result(s): A) Mean LH/FSH ratio, fasting and postprandial blood sugar, fasting and postprandial insulin levels, serum testosterone, HOMA-IR calculated: (1) In Metformin group: 2.14 +/- 0.74, 92.04 +/- 7.82, 125.66 +/- 14.16, 16.26 +/- 7.25, 40.36 +/- 21.35, 57.47 +/- 13.84, 3.72 +/- 1.9 respectively pre-treatment and 1.74 +/- 0.49, 89.5 +/- 6.02, 123.04 +/- 10.23, 14.15 +/- 4.71, 36.31 +/- 11.27, 54.46 +/- 10.6, 3.1 +/- 1.14 post-treatment respectively. (2) In Myoinositol (MI) treated group: 2.29 +/- 0.69, 93.46 +/- 7.62, 124.06 +/- 14.44, 15.21 +/- 8.83, 41.76 +/- 17.07, 58.02 +/- 14.9, 3.51 +/- 2.13 pre-treatment and 1.91 +/- 0.68, 88.5 +/- 6.96, 121.82 +/- 11.17, 12.09 +/- 5.67, 37.18 +/- 11.17, 56.61 +/- 11.68, 2.58 +/- 1.27 post-treatment respectively. B) Ultrasonographic features seen: (1) left and right ovarian volume: Metformin group: 13.15 +/- 4.22 and 13.58+/- 3.95 pre-treatment improved to 10.54 +/-1.8 and 11.13+/- 1.99 respectively post-treatment. Myo-inositol plus d-chiro inositol group: 11.97 +/- 3.44 and 13.05 +/- 3.67 pretreatment improved to 10.63 +/- 2.21 and 11.4 +/- 2.66 respectively post-treatment. (2) Antral follicle count: In metformin group, reduced from 14.36+/- 3.68 to 10.38 +/-1.98 for left ovary and 15. 52 +/-3.86 to 10.82+/- 2.14 for right ovary. For myoinositol plus d-chiro inositol group, reduced from 13.26 +/- 4.16 to 10.76 +/- 2.42 for left ovary and 14.44 +/- 4.01 to 11.64 +/- 2.81 for right ovary. Conclusion(s): Inositol and metformin significantly improved insulin sensitivity in PCOS and was comparable except for better improvement of HOMA-IR with inositol drug than Metformin. Inositol combination drug can be considered as new treatment option and can be given for long time without having any significant side-effects. Better tolerability of inositol makes it more acceptable for the recovery of androgenic and metabolic profile in PCOS women.
