148. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 635301522
T1  - Effectiveness of myoinositol versus metformin on biochemical profile of women with PCOS
T3  - Royal College of Obstretriscians and Gynaecologists World Congress, RCOG 2021. Virtual.
A1  - Noreen H.
A1  - Un Nisa Rab Nawaz Z.
A1  - Khanum W.
A1  - Syed S.
A1  - Saleem H.
A1  - Tanveer I. 
Y1  - 2021//
N2  - Introduction Polycystic Ovarian Syndrome (PCOS) is the commonest endocrine disorder in women of reproductive age, characterized by increased secretion of androgens, oligomenorrhea, anovulatory cycles, dyslipidemia and resistance to insulin. Various medical agents are being used to optimize the biochemical profile in such women. Previously metformin was used but it is less tolerable due to its side effects. Myoinositol is a naturally occurring substance with insulin sensitizing capabilities. Objectives To compare the effectiveness of myoinositol versus metformin on biochemical profile in women with PCOS. Materials & methods A randomized control trial was conducted in Department of OBGYN, BBH Rawalpindi for 06 months from 17th Oct 2019 to 16th April 2020. A total of 100 women with PCOS having age from 18 to 35 years were included. Patients with hypothyroidism, hyperprolactinemia and chronic renal failure were excluded. The patients presented with PCOS were divided into two groups. Group A was given myoinositol 1 gram twice daily and Group B took metformin 500 mg thrice daily for 24 weeks. Hormonal profile like FSH, LH and LH/FSH ratio and Fasting blood glucose were measured at baseline and at 24 weeks. Results In Metformin group the women of ages 18-25 and 26-35 years were 46% and 54%, respectively. In Myoinositol group the ratio was 48% and 52% respectively. In Metformin treated group mean LH, FSH, LH/FSH ratio and Fasting blood sugar was 7.65 +/- 2.79, 5.19 +/- 1.79, 1.54 +/- 0.68 and 90.82 +/- 10.72 respectively at baseline and 6.16 +/- 2.57, 4.34 +/- 1.65, 1.50 +/- 0.68 and 85.96 +/- 5.72 after 24 weeks. In Myoinositol (MI) treated group mean LH, FSH, LH/FSH ratio and Fasting blood sugar was 6.37 +/- 3.90, 4.66 +/- 1.37, 1.51 +/- 1.29 and 88.52 +/- 11.13 at baseline and 4.54 +/- 2.56, 3.71 +/- 1.39, 1.37 +/- 1.05 and 88.10 +/- 4.43 after 24 weeks of treatment respectively Conclusion The myoinositol is better than metformin in improving the biochemical profile in PCOS. It has better tolerability as compared to metformin.
