283. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 624607406
T1  - Induccion de ovulation em sindrome de ovario poliquistico/ovarian stimulation for pcos patientes
T3  - 22nd FIGO World Congress of Gynecology and Obstetrics. Rio de Janeiro Brazil.
A1  - Dale L.F. 
Y1  - 2018//
N2  - PCOS patients have in common Insulin resistance syndrome yielding to anovulation status, high androgen signs, obesity, but in some cases with not all the symptoms together. Many treatments were used in the past with poor results, like ovary surgery, oral contraception, antiestrogens inductors. Clomifem Citrate was used for long time, but some secondary effects limited its use. Thin endometrium and poor cervical mucus, maybe responsible for a poor pregnancy rate in comparison with the successs of ovulation. Aromatase inhibitors has shown better results in pregnancy rates. Inositol, a new drug, may replace metformin, in the metabolic treatment of PCOS. Combining low dose Gonadotrophins and aromatase inhibitor has been used for ovulation induction with good results.
