346. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 611210011
T1  - Genetic, hormonal and metabolic aspects of PCOS: An update
A1  - De Leo V.
A1  - Musacchio M.C.
A1  - Cappelli V.
A1  - Massaro M.G.
A1  - Morgante G.
A1  - Petraglia F. 
Y1  - 2016//
N2  - Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is a complex endocrine disorder affecting 5-10 % of women of reproductive age. It generally manifests with oligo/anovulatory cycles, hirsutism and polycystic ovaries, together with a considerable prevalence of insulin resistance. Although the aetiology of the syndrome is not completely understood yet, PCOS is considered a multifactorial disorder with various genetic, endocrine and environmental abnormalities. Moreover, PCOS patients have a higher risk of metabolic and cardiovascular diseases and their related morbidity, if compared to the general population.Copyright © 2016 The Author(s).
