431. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 71476549
T1  - A study of the effects of myoinositol administration on clinical, endocrine and psychosomatic parameters in polycystic ovarian syndrome
T3  - RCOG World Congress 2014. Hyderabad India.
T3  - (var.pagings).
A1  - Tilwani K.
A1  - Tilwani S. 
Y1  - 2014//
N2  - Introduction Polycystic ovarian syndrome is one of the most common endocrine disorders seen in females of reproductive age group. It is typically characterised by hyperandrogenism, chronic anovulation and insulin-resistance. Polycystic ovarian syndrome has a myriad of clinical, endocrine and psychosomatic manifestations. Of late, manifestations of polycystic ovarian syndrome have been observed, probably owing to neurohormonal changes. Methods This is a study of 50 patients suffering from polycystic ovarian syndrome who were administered myoinositol 2 gm twice a day for a period of 12 weeks. A detailed comparative profile comprising of the patients' clinical, biochemical, hormonal and psychosomatic parameters of all these patients at pre-treatment and post-treatment stages have been compared. Results After 12 weeks of administration of myoinositol, there was a significant improvement in the patients' clinical, biochemical, hormonal and psychosomatic parameters. Conclusion Myoinositol improves the reproductive axis functioning in patients suffering from polycystic ovarian syndrome and also corrects the metabolic, hormonal and psychosomatic abnormalities. Myinositol is useful in the treatment of polycystic ovarian syndrome. Soruces of funding: Patients have funded their own medication and investigations and the data has been complied at our own office.
