T1  - Myoinositol-adjuvant therapy in PCOS
T3  - Mioinozitol-terapie adjuvanta in cadrul stimularii ovarelor micropolichistice
A1  - Veliscu A.
A1  - Marinescu B.
A1  - Damian C.
A1  - Costoiu L.
A1  - Moisa A. 
Y1  - 2012//
N2  - Despite the fact that PCOS is the most common endocrinopathy,the basal mechanism has not been fully understood.Traditionally it was useful to belive that PCOS exists due to a vicious cercle that can be initiatead to several entry points. No matter of what the theories that are proposed, thare is the same result:angrogenal hormone excess and anovulation.The lack of ovarian response to stimulation, the ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome or imature oocytes are bodersome for the specialists that deal with infertility.Myoinositol is an adjuvant therapy in IVF or as a sole therapy in inducing ovulation.This substance, considered to be from the group of vitamins B acts mainly by increasing insulin sensitivity and by improvening the insulin receptor pathway.Due to myoinositol the FSH/LH ratio is modified, the testosteron and insulin levels are decreasing and the normal menstrual ciclicity is restablished.
