490. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 362035111
ID  - 21300338 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21300338]
T1  - The role of inositol supplementation in patients with polycystic ovary syndrome, with insulin resistance, undergoing the low-dose gonadotropin ovulation induction regimen
A1  - Morgante G.
A1  - Orvieto R.
A1  - Di Sabatino A.
A1  - Musacchio M.C.
A1  - De Leo V. 
Y1  - 2011//
N2  - In an attempt to evaluate the role of inositol supplementation in insulin-resistant patients with polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS), undergoing gonadotropin ovulation induction using the low-dose step-down regimen, we conducted a prospective longitudinal study comparing the stimulation characteristics of 15 patients treated with inositol, to a cohort, matched by age and body mass index (BMI), without inositol. Inositol nutritional supplementation produced very good clinical results with a significant reduction in cancellation rate (0 vs. 40%) and the consequent improvement in clinical pregnancy rate (PR) (33.3% vs. 13.3%). © 2011 by American Society for Reproductive Medicine.
