497. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 70462057
T1  - Ovulatory and metabolic benefit with the addition of D-chiro-inositol to polycystic ovary syndrome treatment
T3  - 49th Annual Meeting of the European Society for Paediatric Endocrinology, ESPE 2010. Prague Czechia.
T3  - (var.pagings).
A1  - Raissouni N.
A1  - Galescu O.
A1  - Bhangoo A.
A1  - Ten S. 
A2  - Lebl J.
Y1  - 2010//
N2  - Background: Insulin resistance plays an important pathogenic role in women with Polycystic ovarian syndrome (PCOS). Insulin sensitizer's metformin and D-chiro-inositol has been proposed to ameliorate hyperandrogenemia and ovulatory function in Women with PCOS. Objective and hypotheses: To compare the effectiveness of metformin (M) & D-chiro-inositol (I) combination treatment with metformin treatment alone between lean and obese adolescent with PCOS . Method(s): 44 adolescent's girls were studied (Age from 16 -19 years) NIH guidelines were used for the clinical diagnosis of PCOS. Participants were divided into 4 groups according to BMI (Cut off point for BMI was 25 Kg/ m2) and mode of treatment: Group 1: Overweight PCOS on Metformin (N= 18 ) Group2: lean PCOS on Metformin (N=6 ) Group 3: Overweight on Metformin & I (N=15 ) Group 4: lean control on Metformin &I (N= 5 ) All groups received 2000 mg/day of metformin and Group 3 and Group 4 received 2000mg/day of D-chiro-inositol. Serum steroids, anthropometric parameters ,metabolic parameters and menstrual regularity were compared between groups at Baseline and 6 months after treatment. Result(s): Free testosterone decreased in all groups (P<0.05). Insulin level decreased in all groups except group 4. BMI decreased only in Group 3. Liver function improved in group 1and Vitamin D improved in group 2.(P<0.05) Irregular menstruation normalized in 60% of group 3 and 4, in 5% in group 1 and in 0% in group 2. Systolic BP, LDL, glucose ,FSH , prolactin decreased in group 3 and 4 comparing to group 1 and 2(p<0.05). Clinical improvement was seen after 3 months in Group 3 and after 6 months in Group 1 and 2. (Table presented) Conclusion(s): Adjunctive therapy of D-Chiro- Inositol to Metformin in PCOS treatment reveals more pronounced effect on the metabolic parameters and the ovulatory function in both lean and obese adolescent's girls comparing to Metformin alone. This change has more significance if they persist over long period of time.
