578. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 35452619
T1  - Polycystic ovary syndrome
A1  - Anonymous.
Y1  - 2002//
N2  - Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is a condition of unexplained hyperandrogenic chronic anovulation that most, likely represents a heterogeneous disorder. Its etiology remains unknown, and treatment is largely symptom based and empirical. Recent findings suggest PCOS has substnatial metabolic sequelae, including risk of diabetes and possibly cardiovascular disease, and that primary treatment should focus on metabolic sequelae. The purpose of this document is to examine the best available evidence on the diagnosis and clinical management of PCOS.
